Segro, Aviva Raise $643 Million Loan for APP Fund, CoStar Says

-- B y   S i m o n   P a c k a r d
-- 
2011-09-05T15:08:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/segro-aviva-raise-643-million-loan-for-app-fund-costar-says.html
Airport Property Partnership, the
venture between  Segro Plc (SGRO)  and Aviva Investors, raised a 400
million-pound ($643 million) senior loan backed by its real
estate,  CoStar Group  said, citing people familiar with the deal.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  led a group of five banks making the
loan, which refinances debt that was maturing, CoStar, a real
estate information service, reported. Aside from HSBC, the new
lenders are Barclays Plc, Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc, BNP
Paribas SA, Credit Agricole SA and Banco Santander SA, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Packard in London at 
 packard@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Blackman at   ablackman@bloomberg.net  